## Bug Report

**Current Behavior**
Babel breaks the swapping of two variable values using array destructuring. This only seems to happen if the two values to be swapped are also function arguments.

**Input Code**
Correct Behaviour: [REPL version 7.0.0-beta.39](https://babeljs.io/en/repl#?babili=false&browsers=&build=&builtIns=false&spec=false&loose=false&code_lz=GYVwdgxgLglg9mABDAzgIQKZQO4Y2ACgA8AaRAQzICMBKRAbwChFlhEDzEA-RWxAbUq8AuogC8AqmXLCA3M0QAnLCEVIi3CogBk2xBoA8veQF9GQA&debug=false&forceAllTransforms=false&shippedProposals=false&circleciRepo=&evaluate=false&fileSize=false&timeTravel=false&sourceType=module&lineWrap=true&presets=env&prettier=false&targets=&version=7.0.0-beta.39&envVersion=7.0.0-beta.39)

Incorrect Behaviour: [REPL version 7.0.0-rc.2](https://babeljs.io/repl/build/master#?babili=false&browsers=&build=&builtIns=false&spec=false&loose=false&code_lz=GYVwdgxgLglg9mABDAzgIQKZQO4Y2ACgA8AaRAQzICMBKRAbwChFlhEDzEA-RWxAbUq8AuogC8AqmXLCA3M0QAnLCEVIi3CogBk2xBoA8veQF8gA&debug=false&forceAllTransforms=false&shippedProposals=false&circleciRepo=&evaluate=false&fileSize=false&timeTravel=false&sourceType=module&lineWrap=true&presets=env&prettier=false&targets=&version=7.0.0-rc.2&envVersion=7.0.0-rc.2)

```js
function isBetween(x, a, b) {
  if (a > b) [a, b] = [b, a];
  return x > a && x < b;
}
```

**Babel Configuration (.babelrc, package.json, cli command)**

```js
{
  presets: [['@babel/preset-env', {
    targets: {browsers: ['> 1%', 'not ie <= 11', 'not ios < 10']},
    modules: false,
    useBuiltIns: false,
    loose: true
  }]]
};
```

**Environment**
- Babel version: v7.0.0-rc.2
- Node/npm version: Node 8/npm 5
